{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17512629","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17512629"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T12:57:58+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T12:57:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11929"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"11929","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/11929"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.15,0.1,0.05,0.22,0.48]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4525"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78132"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4525","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4525"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11929"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63554"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"39"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"88"},{"type":"tags","id":"1058"},{"type":"tags","id":"1674"},{"type":"tags","id":"2701"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"8118"},{"type":"tags","id":"9824"},{"type":"tags","id":"10964"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"6674"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6704"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26792"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78132","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78132"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 80-year-old-woman is currently being treated for decompensated heart failure. Her clinical condition has been improving but a few days later, she develops a productive cough and new oxygen requirement. Chest X-ray shows lobar consolidation and she is commenced on intravenous antibiotics. Soon after the first dose, she develops hypotension, tachycardia and acute shortness of breath.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following tests is used to determine the cause of her most recent symptoms?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["RAST test","NT-proBNP","Oral challenge test with the same antibiotic","Serum total IgE","Serum tryptase"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe current clinical presentation is consistent with anaphylaxis, likely caused by antibiotics.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESerum tryptase \u003C/strong\u003Ecan help to identify whether the cause is due to anaphylaxis and if the level is elevated, it is highly suggestive of anaphylaxis. This can reduce the need for other investigations of other causes which have overlapping presentations. Examples include severe asthma exacerbations, myocardial infarction, and acute pulmonary oedema. However, a normal tryptase level does not exclude the diagnosis of anaphylaxis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERAST test \u003C/strong\u003Eis not indicated in the acute setting. It is a test to detect IgE antibodies against specific allergens that the person is allergic to.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENT-proBNP \u003C/strong\u003Eis useful to support the diagnosis of heart failure and also a good predictor of left ventricular ejection fraction. It is not useful to support the diagnosis of anaphylaxis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOral challenge test with the same antibiotic \u003C/strong\u003Eis not suitable in an acute setting as it may potentially trigger another anaphylactic reaction. Oral challenge tests are typically carried out in a controlled environment by allergists where treatment for anaphylaxis is easily accessible.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESerum total IgE\u003C/strong\u003E will not be accurate in the diagnosis of anaphylaxis as it can be elevated from multiple factors including prior exposure to other allergens.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Anaphylaxis is diagnosed based on the clinical presentation in the acute setting.","Serum tryptase is a useful test to confirm anaphylaxis, especially when the diagnosis is uncertain."],"references":["Amitava Dasgupta, Amer Wahed, Chapter 8 - Cardiac Markers, Editor(s): Amitava Dasgupta, Amer Wahed, Clinical Chemistry, Immunology and Laboratory Quality Control, Elsevier, 2014, Pages 127-144, ISBN 9780124078215, https://doi.org/10.1016/B978-0-12-407821-5.00008-5. (https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/B9780124078215000085)","National Clinical Guideline Centre (UK). Drug Allergy: Diagnosis and Management of Drug Allergy in Adults, Children and Young People. London: National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE); 2014 Sep. (NICE Clinical Guidelines, No. 183.) 7, Measuring serum tryptase after suspected anaphylaxis. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK274147/","Oettgen HC. Fifty years later: Emerging functions of IgE antibodies in host defense, immune regulation, and allergic diseases. J Allergy Clin Immunol. 2016 Jun;137(6):1631-1645. doi: 10.1016/j.jaci.2016.04.009. PMID: 27263999; PMCID: PMC4898788. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27263999/","Australian Society of Clinical Immunology and Allergy. ASCIA Guidelines - Acute Management of Anaphylaxis. [Internet]. Accessed on 9 Jan 2025. Available from: https://www.allergy.org.au/hp/papers/acute-management-of-anaphylaxis-guidelines"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63554"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11929"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63554","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63554"},"attribut